  coaching_execution = '{"movement_description":"Step to a long lunge from plank, add controlled reach or rotation, then return to plank without losing trunk position.","setup":["Choose the regression or leverage that lets the athlete perform World''s Greatest Stretch to Plank without pain.","Set the surface, support, wall, bar, box, or mat so it cannot move unexpectedly.","Start in the base body position with ribs, pelvis, shoulders, and hands/feet organized before the first rep."],"execution_steps":["Create tension before moving.","Step to a long lunge from plank, add controlled reach or rotation, then return to plank without losing trunk position.","Move through only the range the athlete can own.","Return or reset with the same posture and control used at the start.","Stop the set when the quality gate is no longer met."],"coach_cues":["Step outside hand","Back leg long","Reach and breathe","Return under control"],"athlete_cues":["Long lunge, long reach."],"breathing_cues":["Exhale through the hard part without breath-holding.","Keep breathing quiet enough that posture does not change."],"common_faults":["Short lunge","Collapsed plank","Bouncing the stretch","Knee pain from poor line"],"quality_gate":["No pain, numbness, dizziness, or pressure symptoms.","Joint positions remain aligned through the intended range.","The athlete can finish the rep or hold without rushing, collapsing, or compensating.","The next repetition would look the same as the first."],"stop_signs":["Pain appears or increases.","The athlete loses the required body shape or joint position.","Grip, wrist, shoulder, trunk, hip, knee, or ankle control fails.","The athlete cannot breathe or safely exit the position."]}'::jsonb,
